Description: Blue-glazed steatite scarab, clypeus marked, feathered legs, longitudinally pierced, base inscribed with name of Mistress of the House Amenemhat Senbit.
Curator's comments: Martin, Egyptian Admin and Private-name Seals (1971) cat no.181 [33.13].
Bibliographic references: Martin 1971 / Egyptian administrative and private-name seals, principally of the Middle Kingdom and Second Intermediate Period (181)
